; --- progressinband (post-T56 chan_sip parity, tri-state early-media control) ---
; chan_sip semantic: tri-state never/no/yes controlling whether SIP signals
; ringing via 180 Ringing only OR allows in-band audio playback BEFORE 200 OK
; answer. Use case: IVR/announcement playback before answer (e.g. carrier
; "your call cannot be completed as dialed" recordings, custom ringback tones).
;
; Tri-state values:
;   never  (default) - emit 180 Ringing only; never send in-band audio with
;                      provisional response; chan_sofia behavior preserved
;   no               - same effective behavior as never under chan_sofia Option B
;                      partial wire-in (KNOWN LIMITATION below)
;   yes              - emit 180 Ringing + force in-band audio playback (returns
;                      -1 to core which streams audio over RTP per chan_sip
;                      verbatim semantic at chan_sip.c:7631)
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:28166-28172 verbatim per-peer parser via
; handle_common_options indirection (L29544 [general] call site shares parser
; with L28671 per-peer call site) + sip.h:282-285 verbatim 3 macros (SIP_PROG_
; INBAND (3<<25) + SIP_PROG_INBAND_NEVER (0<<25) + SIP_PROG_INBAND_NO (1<<25)
; + SIP_PROG_INBAND_YES (2<<25)) + chan_sip.c:7616-7637 verbatim use site at
; sip_indicate AST_CONTROL_RINGING + chan_sip.c:19425 verbatim "Progress inband"
; sip show settings display.
