; --- autoframing (post-T56 chan_sip parity, PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY ship) ---
; chan_sip semantic: when set, honor peer-advertised ptime/maxptime in inbound
; SDP via ast_codec_pref_setsize for codec packetization size. When clear
; (default), use fixed ptime from format prefs (chan_sip.c:12663 force config
; ptime via ast_rtp_codecs_packetization_set on incoming call).
;
; Use case: codec ptime negotiation for narrow-bandwidth scenarios with ptime-
; sensitive codecs (G.729/G.726 with non-default framesizes; e.g. G.729 with
; ptime=10 vs default ptime=20 for bandwidth optimization).
