; chan_sip semantic: chan_sip-CLIENT outbound SUBSCRIBE refresh-timer for
; subscribing TO another server's MWI; chan_sip.c:13378 sets mwi->call->
; expiry; chan_sip.c:21749 ast_sched_add(sched, mwi_expiry * 1000, ...) for
; refresh interval. chan_sofia uses field for SERVER-side outbound NOTIFY
; Expires header per RFC 6665 (T55 notifier at chan_sofia.c:8339) — same
; time interval, different direction; same field serves both purposes
; correctly.
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:29775-29782 verbatim [general] dual-
; key parser (mwiexpiry + mwiexpirey alternate spelling — BOTH spellings
; parsed identically via OR-chained acceptance) + chan_sip.c:570 verbatim
; static int mwi_expiry + sip.h:58 verbatim DEFAULT_MWI_EXPIRY = 3600.
; Backup-fork verification (chan_sip.c.bk L561+L29514-29517) CONFIRMED chan_
; sip-parity-NOT-fork-regression-class.
;
; chan_sofia 3-spelling OR-chained acceptance:
;   * mwi_expiry  — chan_sofia T55.1 historical (with underscore)
;   * mwiexpiry   — chan_sip primary verbatim spelling
;   * mwiexpirey  — chan_sip alternate spelling (typo preserved for drop-in
;                   compat — operators historically use either)
; All 3 spellings parse identically into sofia_cfg.mwi_expiry int field.
;
; **NOT PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY** — full chan_sip-faithful semantic active
; immediately via T55.1 wire-in (chan_sofia infrastructure-PRESENT enabled
; reduced parser-naming-fix scope per Pattern 14 source-correction at R-ACK
; analogous to domainsasrealm 5fbee76 chan_sofia-domain-list-infrastructure-
; PRESENT precedent). Parser extension achieves chan_sip drop-in compat
; without breaking T55.1 chan_sofia-naming work.
;
; chan_sofia surpass: sip show settings displays "MWI expiry: %d" at
; runtime — chan_sip silent at this CLI (chan_sip does NOT display
; mwi_expiry at sip show settings; verified via grep). chan_sofia helper-
; architecture-advantage 19th-instance CLI-exposure-where-chan_sip-silent
