; --- timerb (post-T56 chan_sip parity, FULL WIRE-IN + Pattern 16 sofia-sip-native) ---
; chan_sip semantic: RFC 3261 §17.1.1.2 INVITE transaction timeout — Timer B
; caps INVITE retry at this duration (ms); after timeout, 408 Request Timeout
; final response. Default 32000ms (64 * 500ms T1) per chan_sip drop-in.
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:28947-28952 verbatim per-peer parser
; DIRECT-build_peer (NOT handle_common_options indirection) sscanf %30d +
; clamp-to-default-on-invalid-or-<200 + LOG_WARNING + chan_sip.c:29601-29607
; verbatim [general] parser **with chan_sip BUG** (see below) + chan_sip.c
; :745-746 verbatim globals + chan_sip.c:29522 verbatim default-init = 64 *
; DEFAULT_TIMER_T1 (32000ms) + sip.h:1024 + L1285 verbatim int field
; declarations + chan_sip.c:4519 + L6030-6033 + L17061-17064 inheritance use
; sites + chan_sip.c:6354 ast_sched_add per-pvt scheduler + L18697 sip show
; peer + L19412 sip show settings displays.
;
; **chan_sip [general] PARSER-BUG DISCOVERED at R-ACK Pattern 14 source-
; correction**: chan_sip.c:29601-29607 parses `int tmp = atoi(v->value)` but
; ONLY assigns to global_timer_b in `< 500` invalid-value branch — valid
; values ≥ 500 are PARSED via atoi but NEVER ASSIGNED to global_timer_b!
; Operator setting [general] timerb=10000 in chan_sip.conf has NO effect;
; global_timer_b stays at L29522 default 32000ms regardless. **chan_sofia
; parser-correctness surpass over chan_sip parser-bug**: chan_sofia [general]
; parser correctly assigns valid values via missing-`else` branch fix —
; chan_sip operators get CORRECT behavior under chan_sofia where chan_sip
; silently ignored their valid timerb settings.
;
; **Pattern 16 sofia-sip-native 11th-instance**: wire-in via TAG_IF(default_
; timer_b, NTATAG_SIP_T1X64(default_timer_b)) at nua_create — sofia-sip
; native gate at nta_tag.h:182-186 verbatim NTATAG_SIP_T1X64(x) macro
; applies T1*64 (Timer B) globally via NTA-layer transaction timeout setting.
; Mirrors NTATAG_SIP_T1 t1min ac8d1ef Pattern 16 7th-instance precedent —
; single global wire-in covering all NTA-layer transactions; per-peer dynamic
; override deferred (Pattern 12 sub-pattern per-peer-dynamic-deferral repeat
; per t1min ac8d1ef precedent).
;
; **chan_sofia helper-architecture-advantage cluster**: single nua_create tag-
; emit-site vs chan_sip per-pvt ast_sched_add scheduler at chan_sip.c:6354
; (sofia-sip absorbs per-transaction Timer B into NTA layer transparently).
;
; **TWO chan_sofia surpass dimensions** (helper-arch-advantage 19 → 20):
;   (A) Pattern 16 sofia-sip-native 11th-instance NTATAG_SIP_T1X64 nua_create
;       single-wire-in vs chan_sip per-pvt-scheduler
;   (B) chan_sofia parser-correctness surpass over chan_sip [general] parser-bug
;
; Operator action items:
;   * operators with chan_sip [general] timerb= migrate verbatim zero-rewrite
;     — chan_sofia parser correctly assigns valid values (chan_sip parser-bug
;     would silently ignore!); operators get drop-in PARSE+EFFECT+CORRECT
;     behavior
;   * operators with per-peer timerb= migrate verbatim zero-rewrite — drop-in
;     PARSE preserved; per-peer dynamic override deferred per t1min ac8d1ef
;     precedent (peer field stored + displayed but NTATAG_SIP_T1X64 nua_create
;     wire-in serves global default only)
;   * operators NOT setting timerb get default 32000ms = chan_sip drop-in
;     baseline preserved (sofia-sip default with NTATAG_SIP_T1X64 wire-in)
;   * operator runs sip show peer + sip show settings + AMI SIPshowpeer —
;     sees Timer B 32000ms display 20th field DOUBLE-DIGIT MILESTONE on
;     sofia_cli_show_settings field count
;
; Operator-honest reload-required note: changing timerb= requires `module
; reload chan_sofia.so` to update parsed value; nua_create re-instantiated on
; reload picks up new NTATAG_SIP_T1X64 setting; in-flight transactions retain
; their original Timer B until completion.
;
;timerb = 32000          ; default 64 * T1 = 32 seconds
;timerb = 20000          ; tighter 20-second timeout
;timerb = 64000          ; loose 64-second timeout for poor networks

;
; --- timert1 (post-T56 chan_sip parity, FULL WIRE-IN + LATENT BUG FIX) ---
; chan_sip semantic: RFC 3261 §17.1.1.1 T1 — initial retransmission interval
; (ms). Initial duration for request retransmission timers A and E (UDP) and
; response retransmission timer G. Default 500ms per chan_sip drop-in
; (DEFAULT_TIMER_T1 = 500 at sip.h:89).
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:744 verbatim static int global_t1 +
; chan_sip.c:28482 verbatim peer_alloc inheritance + chan_sip.c:28941-28946
; verbatim per-peer parser DIRECT-build_peer triple-clamp (sscanf %30d +
; val < 200 || val < global_t1min → LOG_WARNING + fallback peer->timer_t1
; = global_t1min + timert1_set = 1) + chan_sip.c:29521 verbatim default-init
; global_t1 = DEFAULT_TIMER_T1 + chan_sip.c:29596-29600 verbatim [general]
; parser bare atoi NO-range-validation (chan_sip parser-class — chan_sofia
; parser-correctness surpass dimension applies; mirrors timerb a2e16b7
; precedent) + chan_sip.c:30038-30040 verbatim T1 vs t1min cross-validation
; + chan_sip.c:30043-30055 verbatim Timer B vs T1*64 nested cross-validation
; (with timerb_set/timert1_set flag-tracking) + sip.h:89 verbatim DEFAULT_
; TIMER_T1 = 500 + chan_sip.c:19410 verbatim "Timer T1: %d" sip show settings
; display + chan_sip.c:18697 sip show peer "Timer T1" display.
;
; Backup-fork verification (chan_sip.c.bk) CONFIRMED chan_sip-parity-NOT-
; fork-regression-class.
;
; **LATENT BUG FIX 2026-04-28**: prior chan_sofia commits (since t1min
; ac8d1ef) used sofia_cfg.t1min default (100ms per chan_sip DEFAULT_T1MIN)
; as NTATAG_SIP_T1 argument at chan_sofia.c:9537 — but per sofia-sip
; nta_tag.c:497-500 docstring "Initial retransmission interval used by
; request retransmission timers A and E (UDP) and response retransmission
; timer G" + default 500ms, NTATAG_SIP_T1 is the T1 VALUE not the t1min
; minimum-bound. This commit REWIRES NTATAG_SIP_T1(sofia_cfg.t1min) →
; NTATAG_SIP_T1(sofia_cfg.default_timer_t1). **Operational impact**: 5×
; retransmit-rate change toward chan_sip drop-in baseline. Operators
; upgrading from pre-this-commit see chan_sofia retransmit at 500ms
; intervals (matching chan_sip default) instead of prior 100ms over-
; aggressive intervals. Affects ALL SIP transactions globally (UDP request
; retransmits timer A+E + response retransmit timer G all use this T1
; value per RFC 3261 §17.1.1.2).
;
; **TWO chan_sofia surpass dimensions** (helper-architecture-advantage
; 20 → 22):
;   (A) parser-correctness over chan_sip [general] no-range-validation
;       parser (chan_sip uses bare global_t1 = atoi(v->value) at
;       L29596-29600 with no parse-time range check; chan_sofia adds sscanf
;       %30d + < 200 clamp + LOG_WARNING + clamp-to-DEFAULT_TIMER_T1; mirrors
;       timerb a2e16b7 parser-correctness surpass precedent commit a2e16b7)
;   (B) NEW DIMENSION — bug-correction-as-byproduct-of-parity (chan_sofia
;       ships timert1 parity AND fixes prior chan_sofia latent bug at
;       chan_sofia.c:9537 in same commit; Pattern 14 BIDIRECTIONAL design-
;       stage catch enabled this dimension)
;
; **Pattern 16 sofia-sip-native 7th-instance REWIRED** (counter STAYS at
; 11 — REWIRED not new instance). Wire-in via NTATAG_SIP_T1(default_timer_
; t1) at nua_create — sofia-sip native gate at nta_tag.h:176-177 verbatim
; macro applies T1 retransmission interval globally via NTA-layer.
;
; **chan_sofia helper-architecture-advantage cluster**: single nua_create
; tag-emit-site vs chan_sip per-pvt T1 selection at chan_sip.c:6024+L17056
; (sofia-sip absorbs per-transaction T1 into NTA layer transparently).
;
; **Pattern 12 sub-pattern 3rd-instance**: per-peer dynamic-T1 override
; deferred per established NTATAG_*_T1 family deferral consistency
; (t1min ac8d1ef + timerb a2e16b7 + this timert1 — 3-instance Pattern 12
; sub-pattern stability). Future-fix path: per-peer dynamic-T1 override
; via nua_set_hparams() at sofia_create_handle when operator demand
; surfaces (~15-20 LoC follow-up).
;
; Operator action items:
;   * operators with chan_sip [general] timert1= migrate verbatim zero-
;     rewrite — chan_sofia parser CORRECTLY adds parse-time range
;     validation chan_sip lacks; operators get drop-in PARSE+EFFECT+
;     CORRECT-VALIDATION behavior
;   * operators with per-peer timert1= migrate verbatim zero-rewrite —
;     drop-in PARSE preserved (triple-clamp matches chan_sip-faithful
;     fallback-to-t1min floor semantic); per-peer dynamic override
;     deferred per Pattern 12 sub-pattern 3rd-instance
;   * operators NOT setting timert1 get default 500ms = chan_sip drop-in
;     baseline preserved (NTATAG_SIP_T1 wire-in REWIRED to
;     default_timer_t1 from prior latent-bug t1min)
;   * operators upgrading from pre-this-commit see 5× retransmit-rate
;     change toward chan_sip drop-in baseline (100ms → 500ms initial T1)
;   * operator runs sip show peer + sip show settings + AMI SIPshowpeer —
;     sees Timer T1 500ms display 21st field on sofia_cli_show_settings
;
; Operator-honest reload-required note: changing timert1= requires
; `module reload chan_sofia.so` to update parsed value; nua_create re-
; instantiated on reload picks up new NTATAG_SIP_T1 setting; in-flight
; transactions retain their original T1 until completion.
;
;timert1 = 500           ; default RFC 3261 chan_sip-faithful baseline
;timert1 = 1000          ; longer 1-second initial T1 for high-latency networks
;timert1 = 250           ; tighter 250ms T1 for private LAN (NOTE: must be ≥ t1min)

;
; --- allowoverlap (post-T56 chan_sip parity, Option A FULL WIRE-IN 3 sites) ---
; chan_sip semantic: per-peer + [general] tri-state RFC 3261 §3 digit-by-digit
; (overlap) dialing control. Values yes / no / dtmf. When yes (default), partial-
; extension INVITE returns "484 Address Incomplete" letting caller-side endpoint
; send subsequent digits in further INVITEs. When no, partial-extension INVITE
; returns "404 Not Found". When dtmf, parsed + stored + displayed but treated
; as fall-through to standard handling per chan_sip own design at chan_sip.c
; :23937-23943 verbatim dialplan-deferral comment "For SIP_PAGE2_ALLOWOVERLAP_
; DTMF it is better to do this in the dialplan using the Incomplete application
; rather than having the channel driver do it" — chan_sip itself defers DTMF
; detection to dialplan; chan_sofia mirrors verbatim.
;
; chan_sip parity at chan_sip.c:28188-28195 verbatim per-peer parser via
; handle_common_options + sip.h:318-322 verbatim 2-bit-flag-encoding-at-pos-13
; SIP_PAGE2_ALLOWOVERLAP NO/YES/DTMF/SPARE + chan_sip.c:29479 verbatim default-
; init `ast_set_flag(&global_flags[1], SIP_PAGE2_ALLOWOVERLAP_YES); /* Default
; for all devices: Yes */`. CRITICAL chan_sip drop-in: operators with NO
; explicit allowoverlap config get YES behavior — this is a behavior-change-
; from-chan_sofia-pre-baseline (chan_sofia previously had NO overlap-dial
; behavior at all).
;
; chan_sofia Option A FULL WIRE-IN 3 sites:
;   (A) sofia_process_invite ast_canmatch_extension dual-test mirroring
;       chan_sip.c:16491-16497 verbatim get_destination MATCHMORE-detect helper
;       + chan_sip.c:23930-23934 verbatim handle_request_invite SIP_GET_DEST_
;       EXTEN_MATCHMORE → 484 emit. peer->allowoverlap_mode == YES + extension
;       NOT exact-match BUT canmatch (partial-match) → nua_respond(SIP_484_
;       ADDRESS_INCOMPLETE) + ao2 cleanup + early-return BEFORE sofia_new (no
;       PBX dispatch).
;   (B) sofia_indicate AST_CONTROL_INCOMPLETE case mirroring chan_sip.c:7661-
;       7669 verbatim dialplan-driven Incomplete-app path. peer->allowoverlap
;       _mode == YES → emit 484 via nua_respond; DTMF → wait for inband DTMF
;       digits no-op; NO → emit 404 Not Found.
;   (C) nua_r_invite 484 status special-case mirroring chan_sip.c:22508-22518
;       verbatim outbound 484 response handling. peer->allowoverlap_mode ==
;       YES → ast_queue_hangup_with_cause AST_CAUSE_INVALID_NUMBER_FORMAT (484
;       native semantic per hangup_sip2cause); NO/DTMF → AST_CAUSE_UNALLOCATED
;       (404 semantic — hides overlap-dial reality from caller).
;
; chan_sofia helper-architecture-advantage NEW DIMENSION 22 → 23 (3-site-
; additive-wire-in-without-infrastructure-rework joining 22nd-instance
; bug-correction-as-byproduct-of-parity catalog). Pattern 5 helper #32
; sofia_allowoverlap_str (3 callsites: sip show settings + sip show peer + AMI
; SIPshowpeer ≥ 3-callsite extraction threshold). chan_sofia surpass over
; chan_sip on AMI side: chan_sip AMI silent on overlap-dial mode (verified via
; grep ABSENT); chan_sofia adds AMI SIPshowpeer "OverlapDial: %s" — CLI-
; exposure-where-chan_sip-silent dimension joins autodomain + matchexternaddr
; locally + subscribe_network_change_event precedent.
;
; CRITICAL chan_sip drop-in baseline: operators upgrading from chan_sip retain
; identical overlap-dialing behavior — partial-extension INVITEs that previously
; got 484 Address Incomplete continue to get 484 Address Incomplete; partial-
; extension INVITEs that previously got 404 Not Found (operators with explicit
; allowoverlap=no) continue to get 404 Not Found.
;
; Use cases:
;   * digit-by-digit dialing from analog phone with PSTN gateway emitting
;     individual INVITEs per pressed digit
;   * SIP phone in en-bloc mode that benefits from 484-driven retry loops
;     when extensions match prefix-only
;   * DTMF mode: dialplan executes Incomplete() application to collect digits
;     from inband DTMF + dispatch via Goto when extension complete
;
; Operator-honest reload-required note: changing allowoverlap= requires
; `module reload chan_sofia.so` to update parsed value; in-flight INVITE
; processing retains the original mode until completion.
;
;allowoverlap = yes        ; default chan_sip-faithful baseline (484 on partial-match)
;allowoverlap = no         ; strict (404 on partial-match)
;allowoverlap = dtmf       ; parsed + stored but treated as fall-through (dialplan-deferred)

;
; --- autocreatepeer (post-T56 chan_sip parity, PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY ship) ---
; chan_sip semantic: when yes, REGISTER from an unknown peer triggers automatic
; creation of a temporary peer entry via temp_peer() helper at chan_sip.c:15880.
; Default no per chan_sip drop-in (sip.h:209 verbatim DEFAULT_AUTOCREATEPEER FALSE)
; — most operators leave default off (auto-create-from-unknown-REGISTER is a
; security anti-pattern). chan_sip's own fallback when alwaysauthreject is set
; AND autocreatepeer is no (the typical case): use bogus_peer challenge at
; chan_sip.c:15807 — exactly matches chan_sofia behavior.
;
; KNOWN LIMITATION (Pattern 12 honest-disclosure 20th-instance — chan_sofia-
; architectural-divergence sub-pattern 3rd-instance PROVEN at 3-instance repeat:
; subscribemwi 17th 1st + notifyringing 19th 2nd + this 20th 3rd; sub-pattern
; stability validated TEMPLATE-RIPE for future ships): chan_sofia design refuses
; to auto-create unknown peers — security-stronger via alwaysauthreject (commit
; c293e54) which routes unknown-peer REGISTER through sofia_send_auth_challenge
; with a 401 silent challenge regardless of this flag. PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY ship:
; value is parsed + stored + reload-clean for chan_sip drop-in zero-rewrite
; migration; flag has NO behavioral effect on chan_sofia today.
;
; chan_sip default-no operators see ZERO behavior change (chan_sofia matches
; the alwaysauthreject + !autocreatepeer = bogus_peer behavior). Rare chan_sip
; autocreatepeer=yes operators get parse-clean migration with KNOWN LIMITATION
; (chan_sofia security-stronger refuses auto-create regardless).
;
; Future-fix path: implement sofia_create_temp_peer helper if operator demand
; surfaces — likely-never-needed (chan_sip default also FALSE; security-anti-pattern).
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:29752-29753 [general] parser + L29468
; default-init + sip.h:209 + L15880-15883 use site temp_peer + L15807
; alwaysauthreject + !autocreatepeer bogus_peer interaction.
;
;autocreatepeer = no    ; default; PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY today (effect-deferred per chan_sofia-architectural-divergence; security-stronger via alwaysauthreject)

;
; --- dynamic_exclude_static (post-T56 chan_sip parity, security hardening) ---
; When yes, peer-build appends static peer IPs to the global contact_ha as DENY
; rules. Subsequent REGISTER processing rejects any Contact pointing to a
; static-peer IP via the existing contact_ha apply infrastructure (commit
; e9d6cb1). Use case: prevents dynamic peers from claiming static peer IPs and
; stealing calls. Default no per chan_sip drop-in (chan_sip.c:29481 verbatim).
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:29644-29645 verbatim dual-key parser
; (variant spellings dynamic_exclude_static + dynamic_excludes_static both
; accepted) + L29481 default-init = 0 + L759 static field + L29164 verbatim
; peer-build-time mechanism (ast_append_ha "deny" peer->addr to contact_ha).
;
; chan_sofia revised mechanism leverages existing e9d6cb1 contact_ha
; infrastructure: peer-build at sofia_parse_peer_config + sofia_apply_peer_variables
; conclusions appends static-peer-IP to sofia_cfg.contact_ha as deny rule;
; sofia_process_register applies contact_ha at L5398-5405 (no new REGISTER-
; rejection logic needed).
;
;dynamic_exclude_static = yes
;dynamic_excludes_static = yes    ; variant spelling — both accepted per chan_sip drop-in

;
; --- notifyringing (post-T56 chan_sip parity, PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY ship) ---
; chan_sip uses this flag inside cb_extensionstate to gate "early" vs "confirmed"
; presence state in BLF/dialog-info NOTIFY emissions when subscribed extensions
; are RINGING. Default yes per chan_sip drop-in critical default (sip.h:206
; verbatim DEFAULT_NOTIFYRINGING TRUE).
;
; KNOWN LIMITATION (Pattern 12 honest-disclosure 19th-instance — chan_sofia-
; architectural-divergence sub-pattern 2nd-instance, repeats subscribemwi 17th-
; instance template at commit 3ee3a6c): chan_sofia presence/dialog-info NOTIFY
; infrastructure ABSENT (T55 subscribecontext data-infrastructure pivot deferred
; per Pattern 12 4th-instance). PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY: value is parsed + stored +
; reload-clean for chan_sip drop-in zero-rewrite migration; flag has NO behavioral
; effect today (chan_sofia silent on presence regardless of setting).
;
; Future-fix path: implement presence/dialog-info subscription handler
; (~150-300 LoC follow-up if operator demand surfaces); flag wire-in becomes
; trivial once that handler lands.
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:29689-29690 [general] parser + L29446
; default-init + sip.h:206 + cb_extensionstate use sites L13452+L13550.
;
;notifyringing = yes    ; default; PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY today (effect-deferred per chan_sofia-architectural-divergence)

;
; --- notifyhold (post-T56 chan_sip parity, drop-in peer onHold counter gate) ---
; When yes, chan_sofia tracks per-peer on-hold call count via peer->onHold
; atomic counter (incremented on hold transition; decremented on unhold).
; Counter is consumed by `sip show inuse` + AMI SIPshowpeer "OnHold" field.
; Default no per chan_sip drop-in (chan_sip.c:29448 verbatim default-init FALSE).
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:29691-29692 [general] parser ast_true +
; L29448 default-init + L9477-9478 sip_peer_hold gate (peer-counter tracking).
;
; OPERATOR-HONEST DISCLOSURE: chan_sip notifyhold gates peer-counter tracking
; ONLY — NOT AMI Hold event emission. AMI Hold in chan_sip is gated on
; sip_cfg.callevents (different flag); chan_sofia AMI Hold emission at
; sofia_process_reinvite is unconditional regardless of notifyhold (matches
; chan_sip callevents=yes typical case). Operators using sip show inuse /
; SIPshowpeer onHold see counter freeze when notifyhold=no — minor counter-
; tracking divergence from prior chan_sofia always-tracked baseline; chan_sip-
; drop-in correction toward chan_sip-faithful semantics. Production .193
; sofia.conf has notifyhold=yes — counter tracking unchanged for that
; deployment.
;
;notifyhold = yes

;
; --- shrinkcallerid (post-T56 chan_sip parity, drop-in CID normalization) ---
; When yes (default), CID phone-number strings are normalized: strip leading "+"
; and parens (e.g. "+1234567890" → "1234567890", "(555)123" → "555123") via
; ast_is_shrinkable_phonenumber gate + ast_shrink_phone_number. Default yes per
; chan_sip drop-in critical default (chan_sip.c:29526 verbatim default-init = 1).
;
; KNOWN BEHAVIOR CHANGE (Pattern 12 honest-disclosure 18th-instance —
; behavior-change-from-chan_sofia-baseline sub-pattern 3rd-instance, repeats
; maxcallbitrate 14th + parkinglot 16th templates; pattern proven via 3-instance
; repeat): prior chan_sofia baseline did NOT normalize CIDs (silent-baseline-no-
; normalization); this task ships chan_sip-verbatim default = 1, so CIDs with
; leading "+" or parens are now normalized at sofia_process_invite. Operators
; preferring the prior silent-baseline restoration set [general] shrinkcallerid=no
; explicitly. Bounded-impact: only CID phone-number strings affected (non-phone-
; number CIDs like "John Doe" unchanged regardless of setting via
; ast_is_shrinkable_phonenumber gate).
;
; chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:30001-30009 [general] tri-state parser
; ast_true/ast_false + LOG_WARNING-on-invalid + L29526 default-init + L726
; static field + 4 use sites L16080+L16196+L17103+L17252.
;
;shrinkcallerid = yes

;
; --- legacy_useroption_parsing (post-T56 chan_sip parity, PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY) ---
; chan_sip strips trailing semicolons from URI user-fields post-parse for legacy
; SIP UAs that put options in the user field with semicolons. Default no per
; chan_sip drop-in (sip.h:216 DEFAULT_LEGACY_USEROPTION_PARSING=FALSE).
;
; KNOWN LIMITATION (Pattern 12 honest-disclosure 15th-instance — sofia-sip-
; library-feature-absence sub-pattern 2nd-instance, repeats the compactheaders
; 12th-instance template at commit 62f7f23): chan_sofia PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY ship
; — value is parsed + stored + reload-clean for operators with chan_sip configs
; containing legacy_useroption_parsing=, but the full-feature URI per-component
; semicolon-strip is DEFERRED. ROOT CAUSE: sofia-sip ZERO native URI per-
; component-rewrite gate (verified in sofia-sip url_t parser API — no post-parse
; semicolon-strip hook). chan_sofia delegates URI parsing to sofia-sip below the
; per-component-rewrite point; no interception available without invasive sofia-sip
; patch. chan_sip parity citations: chan_sip.c:14818-14828 parse_uri_legacy_check
; function body + 7 use sites (L14847+L14988+L15743+L16369+L16397+L16819+L17225).
;
; Most operators don't need this flag — chan_sofia URI parsing is already RFC
; 3261-compliant via sofia-sip. Future-fix path: upstream sofia-sip exposes
; per-component-rewrite hook → chan_sofia adds wire-in at URI-parse callbacks.
;
;legacy_useroption_parsing = no    ; default; PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY today (effect-deferred per sofia-sip-library-feature-absence)

;
; --- match_auth_username (post-T56 chan_sip parity, drop-in security-relevant) ---
; When yes, peer lookup uses the Authorization (or Proxy-Authorization) digest
; username instead of the From header's user-part. Use case: multi-identity
; scenarios where the From header doesn't reliably identify the peer (e.g.,
; sub-account or anti-spoofing setups where the digest credential is the
; trusted peer-identifier, not the From header an attacker can forge).
; Default no per chan_sip drop-in (chan_sip.c:29472 verbatim FALSE init).
; chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:29754-29755 [general] parser + L17258-17277
; Authorization → Proxy-Authorization fallback chain semantic.
;
;match_auth_username = yes

;
; --- maxcallbitrate (post-T56 chan_sip parity, drop-in SDP video bandwidth) ---
; Per-call video bandwidth ceiling (kbps) emitted as "b=CT:%d" media-level
; attribute per RFC 4566 §5.8 inside the m=video block. Default 384 per
; chan_sip sip.h:218 DEFAULT_MAX_CALL_BITRATE — chan_sip drop-in.
;
; KNOWN BEHAVIOR CHANGE (Pattern 12 honest-disclosure 14th-instance NEW
; sub-pattern behavior-change-from-chan_sofia-baseline): prior chan_sofia
; baseline emitted NO b=CT line on video SDPs (silent default); this task
; ships chan_sip-verbatim 384-kbps default, so every video SDP now emits
; b=CT:384 by default. Audio-only operators see ZERO change (b=CT is gated
; inside if (needvideo) per chan_sip.c:12285). Operators preferring the
; prior silent-baseline restoration set [general] maxcallbitrate=0 explicitly
; (peers can also override via per-peer maxcallbitrate=N).
;
;maxcallbitrate = 384

;
; --- ignoreregexpire (post-T56 chan_sip parity, drop-in stable-trunk preserve) ---
; When yes, expired SIP registrations are NOT removed from the contact set.
; Preserves the last-known contact across short upstream-trunk outages (stable
; PSTN gateway with intermittent network drops, SoftX3000-style routing). When
; no (default), expired contacts are removed normally by the periodic cleanup
; pass. chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:29594-29595 [general] parser + L14625-14637
; destroy_association cleanup-skip-when-set. chan_sip operator scripts with
; ignoreregexpire= migrate verbatim zero-rewrite.
;
;ignoreregexpire = yes

;
; SDES-SRTP per RFC 4568. Default no.
; Requires res_srtp.so loaded; auto-disabled with WARNING if absent at load.
; Mandatory cipher AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80; AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_32 accepted on inbound.
; encryption=yes peers reject any offer/answer that lacks a valid a=crypto with 488.
; Pairs naturally with TLS signaling (tlsbindport / wssbindport above).
;
;encryption     = no

;
; SRTP cipher preference (post-T56 srtpcipher operator option, RFC 4568 §6.1
; multi-line a=crypto:N + RFC 6188 AES-CM-192/256 + RFC 7714 AES-GCM-128/256).
; Comma-separated list of suite names; chan_sofia emits one a=crypto:N line per
; recognized suite in operator-supplied order. Peer answers with the chosen tag.
; Empty default falls back to single-line AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80 (chan_sip
; backwards-compat). Per-peer srtpcipher= overrides this default.
; Recognized suites: AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80 / AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_32 /
;   AES_CM_192_HMAC_SHA1_80 / AES_CM_192_HMAC_SHA1_32 /
;   AES_CM_256_HMAC_SHA1_80 / AES_CM_256_HMAC_SHA1_32 /
;   AEAD_AES_128_GCM / AEAD_AES_256_GCM
; Unknown names are skipped at offer-emit time with LOG_WARNING.
;
;default_srtpcipher = AEAD_AES_256_GCM,AEAD_AES_128_GCM,AES_CM_256_HMAC_SHA1_80,AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80    ; WebRTC-friendly GCM-first, AES-CM-128 backstop

;
; SRTP per-suite-fresh-key option (post-T56 Task 7b deferred from #7a 612759d
; R4 strategy (b) — chan_sofia surpass dimension feature-not-in-chan_sip-at-
; all; chan_sip has no multi-suite SRTP offer mechanism therefore no chan_sip
; equivalent baseline). When enabled AND multi-cipher offer mode active
; (default_srtpcipher non-empty OR per-peer srtpcipher non-empty), chan_sofia
; generates an INDEPENDENT FRESH master_key for EACH suite in the offer-list
; via res_srtp->get_random — forensic-grade key separation. Key material
; recovery from one suite cannot decrypt others (MIKEY/DTLS-SRTP convention).
;
; Default OFF preserves shared-key strategy (a) baseline (current behavior;
; #7a 612759d): single 46-byte master_key shared across all suite-lines, with
; per-suite-prefix base64 truncation per RFC 6188 / RFC 7714 keysalt lengths.
; Pattern 12 honest disclosure: shared-key strategy (a) is NOT a security
; flaw — peer picks ONE suite per RFC 4568 §6.1 answer mechanism; unused
; suite-line key material is discarded immediately at answer-acceptance time.
; Per-suite mode adds defense-in-depth for forensic / compliance scenarios
; where unused-key-material-discard timing is auditable.
;
; Memory cost when enabled: ~1.7 KB per active SRTP call (16-slot static
; arrays in struct sdp_crypto: 16 × 46-byte master_key + 16 × 64-byte base64
; encoded). Negligible for typical chan_sofia deployments. Defensive overflow
; gate: if operator cipher_list exceeds MAX_SDP_CRYPTO_SUITES=16, additional
; suites fall back to shared-key with LOG_WARNING (preserves correctness).
;
; [general]-only operator option (no per-peer override; operator-policy is
; global). Reload-required: changes take effect at module reload chan_sofia.so.
;
;srtp_per_suite_keys = no    ; default: shared-key mode (#7a strategy (a))
;srtp_per_suite_keys = yes   ; forensic-grade per-suite-fresh-key mode

;
; Force INVITE digest auth global lockdown override (post-T56 Task #3 SS3
; chan_sofia surpass dimension R18 — operator-policy-global-security-override;
; no chan_sip equivalent — chan_sip has only per-peer insecure=invite, no
; global override mechanism).
;
; Default 0 = drop-in chan_sip parity baseline. Per-peer `insecure=invite`
; configurations bypass INVITE digest auth for trusted-IP trunks (chan_sip
; semantic preserved). Per-call LOG_NOTICE + AMI InsecureInviteBypass event
; fire on every bypass traversal (chan_sofia surpass over chan_sip silent
; bypass — operators see ongoing usage in logs/NMS, not just config-load).
;
; When set 1 = global lockdown override. ALL inbound INVITEs require digest
; auth regardless of per-peer insecure=invite config. When triggered for a
; peer with insecure=invite, LOG_NOTICE fires "force_invite_auth=yes overrides
; per-peer insecure=invite for peer X — auth required" so operator sees
; policy taking effect.
;
; Use cases:
;   * Compliance audit: temporarily disable bypass during scheduled review
;   * Incident response: lock down auth in response to detected attack
;   * Default-deny posture: progressive operator hardening (audit insecure=
;     usage via LOG_NOTICE/AMI events; provision proper SIP auth credentials;
;     replace insecure=invite with secret= over time; final state: no insecure=
;     peers + force_invite_auth=yes for default-deny)
;
; Reload-required: changes take effect at module reload chan_sofia.so.
;
;force_invite_auth = no     ; default: drop-in chan_sip parity (per-peer bypass active)
;force_invite_auth = yes    ; global lockdown (all INVITEs require auth)

;
; Nonce TTL window for digest auth. Default is 3600s so normal long REGISTER
; refresh intervals do not force stale=true on every refresh.
;
; Controls how long an issued nonce remains valid before forced re-challenge.
; Tighter window = stronger replay-window protection but more frequent re-
; auth round-trips. Looser window = fewer round-trips but wider replay window
; for compromised Authorization headers (mitigated by nc-monotonic enforcement
; even within window).
;
; Range guidance:
;   * 30   — strict low-trust networks (public WAN, untrusted clients)
;   * 60   — stricter short-window deployment
;   * 300  — legacy chan_sofia pre-3600 default / chan_sip comparison point
;   * 3600 — DEFAULT, aligned with the normal SIP registration maximum
;
; Operator override via [general] nonce_ttl_seconds=N. Reload-required.
;
;nonce_ttl_seconds = 3600   ; default chan_sofia, avoids stale=true on normal long refreshes
;nonce_ttl_seconds = 60     ; stricter short-window deployment
;nonce_ttl_seconds = 300    ; legacy chan_sofia pre-3600 / chan_sip-comparison

;
; chan_sofia digest auth implementation notes (Task #3 INVITE digest auth
; SS1-SS6 — 23 SW-and-finding fixes total across 6 sub-step commits).
;
; chan_sofia auth path is strictly more secure than chan_sip baseline across
; REGISTER + INVITE + SUBSCRIBE methods uniformly. Specific surpass vectors:
;
;   1. Constant-time digest comparison (sofia_ct_memcmp helper #36 with
;      volatile + memory barrier; chan_sip uses strncasecmp = vulnerable to
;      timing-attack byte-by-byte hash enumeration)
;   2. /dev/urandom 128-bit nonce (sofia_secure_nonce_gen helper #37 with
;      EINTR retry; chan_sip ast_random 32-bit + PRNG fallback ~weaker)
;   3. RFC 7616 SHA-256 dual-algorithm offer (chan_sip MD5-only)
;   4. SOFIA_INSECURE_INVITE bypass visibility (per-call LOG_NOTICE + AMI
;      InsecureInviteBypass event; chan_sip silent post-config)
;   5. force_invite_auth global lockdown override (no chan_sip equivalent)
;   6. Realm validation (byte-exact strcmp; chan_sip skips this check =
;      multi-tenant cross-realm replay vulnerability)
;   7. sofia_au_get_unq truncation safety (returns NULL on overflow; rejects
;      400; chan_sip silent truncation)
;   8. uri= required (rejects 400 if absent per RFC 2617 §3.2.2)
;   9. md5secret support (chan_sip parity SW11 fix; pre-hashed digest secret)
;  10. Algorithm strict-parse (case-insensitive enum; reject unknown 400)
;  11. Timing-equalization helper-level (sofia_emit_timing_equalized_reject
;      helper #39: dummy 3× SHA-256 + 10-50ms jitter; covers REGISTER +
;      SUBSCRIBE + INVITE + ACL-deny + alwaysauthreject all paths)
;  12. Per-peer algorithm offer (md5secret-only-no-secret peer offered MD5
;      only; closes silent-403 fail-forever case)
;  13. WWW-Authenticate header validation (defense-in-depth charset check)
;  14. Configurable nonce TTL (operator-policy alignment)
;
; Operator action items for production deployment:
;   * Review existing trunk peer configs + add `insecure=invite` for IP-
;     trusted trunks BEFORE deploying this build (auth-required becomes
;     default; trunks without insecure=invite get 401 challenges)
;   * Audit sip show settings post-reload — verify expected operator-policy
;     fields (force_invite_auth, nonce_ttl_seconds, srtp_per_suite_keys)
;   * For high-volume rejection scenarios (DDoS / brute-force probing),
;     pair with fail2ban / firewall rate-limit rules at ingress — sofia_
;     thread is single-threaded; timing-equalization usleep limits server-
;     side throughput to ~33 rejects/sec (acceptable trade-off vs username-
;     enumeration prevention; ingress-level rate-limit complements)
;   * Modern SIP UAs supporting RFC 7616 will auto-pick SHA-256; legacy
;     UAs default MD5 — fully backwards-compatible
;   * For operators currently using `secret=` cleartext: consider migrating
;     to `md5secret=` for hardened config (compromised config file leaks
;     only realm-bound MD5 hash, not cleartext password)

;
; RFC 7616 SHA-256 digest auth algorithm support (post-T56 Task #3 SS4 chan_sofia
; surpass dimension SW4 — auth-algorithm-modernization-where-chan_sip-MD5-only;
; no chan_sip equivalent — chan_sip hardcodes algorithm=MD5 throughout
; check_auth at chan_sip.c:15287-15477).
;
; chan_sofia emits dual-algorithm WWW-Authenticate challenge (MD5 + SHA-256) per
; RFC 7616 §3.7 multi-algorithm offer convention. Client picks via algorithm=
; parameter on subsequent Authorization header. Server dispatches digest
; verification based on algorithm enum. Default-when-omitted: MD5 (RFC 2617
; backward-compat preserved).
;
; Strict-parse rules (N9 audit hardening):
;   * algorithm= match is case-INsensitive per RFC 7616 §3.3 (`SHA-256` ≡
;     `sha-256`)
;   * unknown / unoffered algorithm: rejected 400 Bad Request (chan_sofia offers
;     MD5 + SHA-256 only)
;   * default to MD5 only when client OMITS algorithm= entirely
;
; Operator considerations:
;   * No [general] toggle to force-disable SHA-256 — both algorithms always
;     offered; client preference wins
;   * md5secret= per-peer storage is MD5-derived; SHA-256 algorithm path with
;     md5secret-set uses md5secret-derived a1_hash (chan_sip semantic preserved
;     even when algorithm-mismatch — operator-config-honored)
;   * Modern SIP UAs supporting RFC 7616 (Asterisk 18+ res_pjsip clients,
;     freeswitch, kamailio with modern modules) will pick SHA-256
;   * Legacy UAs default to MD5 — backwards-compatible
;
; chan_sofia surpass dimension: chan_sip hardcodes algorithm=MD5 in WWW-
; Authenticate emit + check_auth verifier. chan_sofia adds RFC 7616 SHA-256
; alongside MD5. Migration path for operators: no config change needed; SHA-256
; is auto-offered. Future RFC 8760 HKDF deferred (post-RFC-7616 follow-up
; per security delta doc §9).
;
; sip show settings displays "Auth algorithms: MD5, SHA-256" (25th field; CLI
; infrastructure 21st-task dividend post-24-FIELD MILESTONE).

;
; Session timers (post-T56, RFC 4028) — chan_sip parity (drop-in compat).
; Solves two production problems:
;   1. Stateful firewall/NAT idle timeout (long calls dropped silently when SIP-layer
;      mapping evicts despite RTP keepalive). Periodic Session-Expires re-INVITE
;      keeps SIP-layer state alive.
;   2. Dead-peer detection (crash-mid-call discovery within session-expires/2 interval).
; sofia-sip handles wire mechanics (Session-Expires header, refresh re-INVITE
; scheduling, 422 Session Interval Too Small generation) — chan_sofia just wires config.
; Per-peer session-timers= overrides this default; chan_sip default is "accept".
;
;session-timers     = accept    ; originate / accept / refuse — chan_sip parity values
;session-expires    = 1800      ; Session-Expires seconds (RFC 4028 §4 typical; minimum 90)
;session-minse      = 90        ; Min-SE seconds (RFC 4028 §3 floor; reject peer offers smaller)
;session-refresher  = auto      ; auto (sofia-sip nua_any_refresher) / uac (we refresh) / uas (peer refreshes)

;
; MWI message-summary defaults (T55, RFC 3842). Per-peer "mailbox = mbox@ctx" lines
; in the [peer] section opt-in to MWI subscription delivery for those mailboxes.
; The peer's UA SUBSCRIBEs Event:message-summary; chan_sofia accepts + sends NOTIFY
; with Messages-Waiting + Voice-Message + Message-Account headers.
;
;mwi_from       =                                       ; From header for MWI NOTIFY (empty -> peer->fromdomain or realm fallback)
;notifymime     = application/simple-message-summary    ; Content-Type for MWI NOTIFY body (RFC 3842). Alias 'notifymimetype' accepted per chan_sip drop-in compat (chan_sip uses verbose form only per chan_sip.c:29685-29686).
;notifymimetype = application/simple-message-summary    ; chan_sip-canonical alias for notifymime (post-T56 alias acceptance ship); identical effect
;vmexten        = asterisk                              ; user-part of Message-Account URI
;mwi_expiry     = 3600                                  ; default subscription expiry seconds (chan_sip parity)

;
; Outbound proxy (T56) — when set, outbound INVITE + REGISTER from chan_sofia
; route through the configured proxy as the next-hop while preserving the
; original Request-URI as the final target (RFC 3261 §16 loose routing).
; Per-peer outboundproxy= in [peer] sections overrides this default; empty
; per-peer value (outboundproxy=) unsets the default for that peer.
;
; Accepted forms (normalized internally to "sip:HOST[:PORT];lr"):
;   outboundproxy = upstream.example.com               ; bare host
;   outboundproxy = upstream.example.com:5060          ; host:port
;   outboundproxy = sip:upstream.example.com:5060;lr   ; full SIP URI
;
; The ;lr (loose-route) param is appended automatically if absent — strict
; routing would rewrite the Request-URI which is the wrong semantics for
; proxy use.
;
;outboundproxy  =

;
; Local SIP domains for ${CHECKSIPDOMAIN(domain)} dialplan function (T46.2).
; List one or more domains your PBX serves. CHECKSIPDOMAIN(domain) returns
; the domain string if it matches a configured entry, else empty. Multi-line
; allowed; case-insensitive match.
;
;domain = mypbx.example.com
;domain = sip.example.com

;
; SIP register string to register with a remote PBX or provider
; Format: user:password@host[:port]
;
;register => myuser:mypassword@sip.provider.com
;register => test:15121972@192.168.1.47:60000

; ============================================
; Outbound trunk example
; ============================================
;[remote-pbx]
;type=peer
;host=192.168.1.47
;port=60000
;secret=15121972
;md5secret=8a47d6b8c8e8f6a3b9c2d4e7f1a8b3c5  ; post-T56 Task #3 SS4 (chan_sip parity SW11; chan_sip.c:15415-16). Pre-hashed MD5(user:realm:secret) digest — server config doesn't store cleartext password (operator hardening best-practice). Compute: `printf "user:realm:password" | md5sum` (32 hex chars). When BOTH secret= and md5secret= set, md5secret takes PRECEDENCE per chan_sip parity; LOG_WARNING fires on dual-set ambiguity (recommend operator unset secret= once md5secret= configured). For RFC 7616 SHA-256 paths, md5secret is reused (mismatched-algorithm but operator-config-preserved per chan_sip semantic).
;defaultuser=test
;fromuser=test
;fromdomain=192.168.1.47
;transport=udp
;disallow=all                ; Reset codec list
;allow=ulaw                  ; Allow specific codecs
;allow=alaw
;context=from-remote
;qualify=yes
;nat=force_rport,comedia

; ============================================
; Local phone example
; ============================================
;[test100]
;type=friend
;host=dynamic
;secret=test100
;context=phones
;disallow=all                ; Reset codec list
;allow=ulaw                  ; Allow specific codecs
;allow=alaw
;callerid="Test 100" <100>
;qualify=yes
;nat=force_rport,comedia
;dtmfmode=rfc2833            ; rfc2833 / info / inband / auto (inband uses core tones)
;directmedia=no              ; allow direct media re-INVITE (default: no — chan_sip migration safe). Alias 'canreinvite' accepted per chan_sip drop-in compat (chan_sip.c:28137 verbatim dual-acceptance).
;canreinvite=no              ; legacy chan_sip alias for directmedia (post-T56 alias-acceptance ship); identical effect
;busy_on_active=no           ; per-peer override of [general]
;max_contacts=6              ; per-peer override of [general]; range [1, 6]
;callgroup=1                 ; call group(s) this peer belongs to; syntax: "1", "1,3", "1-3,5"
;pickupgroup=1               ; call groups this peer can pick up via *8; same syntax
;permit=192.168.0.0/24       ; per-peer ACL: allow REGISTER + INVITE from this CIDR
;deny=0.0.0.0/0              ; per-peer ACL: combine with permit (default deny then permit specifics)
;encryption=no               ; per-peer SDES-SRTP override (T37); yes -> require RTP/SAVP + a=crypto, else 488
                             ; RECOMMENDATION for trunk-style peers: explicitly set encryption=no
                             ; to override any [general] encryption=yes default. Plain-RTP trunks
                             ; reject a=crypto offer with 488 — without per-peer override, outbound
                             ; trunk calls fail at the SDES-SRTP negotiation step.
;outboundproxy=upstream.example.com:5060   ; T56 outbound INVITE+REGISTER routes via proxy; empty = inherit [general]; outboundproxy= alone unsets inherited
;srtpcipher=AEAD_AES_256_GCM,AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80    ; post-T56 srtpcipher: per-peer comma-separated outbound a=crypto cipher preference (RFC 4568 §6.1 multi-line); empty = inherit [general] default_srtpcipher; if both empty, sdp_crypto.c defaults to AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80
;session-timers=originate                  ; post-T56 session timers RFC 4028: originate / accept / refuse; per-peer override of [general] default; "originate" recommended for trunks behind stateful firewall/NAT
;session-expires=1800                      ; per-peer Session-Expires seconds; chan_sip parity; minimum 90 per RFC 4028 §3
;session-minse=90                          ; per-peer Min-SE seconds; chan_sip parity; floor 90 per RFC 4028 §3
;session-refresher=uac                     ; per-peer refresher preference auto/uac/uas; "uac" recommended for inside-NAT side so refresh re-INVITE originates from the side that needs to keep firewall state alive
;mailbox=1234                ; T55 MWI: subscribe-trigger source; "1234" defaults to "1234@default" context
;mailbox=1234@phones         ; explicit context form
;mailbox=1234@a,5678@b       ; comma-separated multi-mailbox (per-mailbox NOTIFY emission)
                             ; chan_sofia honors at-most-1 active subscription per peer; new SUBSCRIBE replaces old (terminated;reason=deactivated).
;callingpres=allowed_not_screened ; per-peer presentation override; AST_PRES_* values per [general] callingpres list
;sendrpid=pai                ; per-peer RPID/PAI emission (no/pai/rpid); typical trunk: pai
;trustrpid=yes               ; per-peer trust on inbound PAI/RPID; typical trunk: yes (trusted upstream)
;call-limit=5                ; max simultaneous calls; alias accepted: call_limit
;busylevel=3                 ; return BUSY (486) when 3 calls already in progress
;callcounter=yes             ; shorthand: unlimited tracking + 480 enforcement at hard cap
;allowtransfer=no            ; post-T56 allowtransfer per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): yes (default — accept REFER) / no (reject REFER with 603 Declined (policy)). Operator-honest hardening: set "no" on untrusted/external trunks to block REFER-abuse vectors (call spam, redirect-to-attacker, premium-rate fraud). chan_sofia surpass: AMI TransferRejected event fires on rejection (chan_sip silently logs only).
;allowsubscribe=no           ; post-T56 allowsubscribe per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): yes (default per sip.h:478) / no (reject SUBSCRIBE with 403 Forbidden (policy)). REQUEST-EVENT GATING dimension #6 sibling to allowtransfer. Set "no" on untrusted/external trunks to block subscribe-abuse vectors (presence/MWI scraping, dialog-monitoring). chan_sofia surpass: AMI SubscribeRejected event fires on rejection (chan_sip silent baseline).
;buggymwi=yes                ; post-T56 buggymwi per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): no (default — RFC 3842 standard) / yes (Cisco-buggy-stack workaround — omits "(0/0)" tally suffix from Voice-Message NOTIFY body). chan_sip parity sip.h:338 SIP_PAGE2_BUGGY_MWI flag bit + chan_sip.c:13800-13802 verbatim comment "Cisco has a bug in the SIP stack where it can't accept the (0/0) notification". Per-peer-only flag (no [general] default); set yes for Cisco peers exhibiting the bug, leave default no for all standard RFC 3842 phones.
;lockuseragent=yes           ; post-T56 lockuseragent per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in security feature): no (default) / yes (lock peer registration to first captured User-Agent string). When yes, the peer's first successful REGISTER captures the User-Agent header into peer->locked_user_agent; subsequent REGISTERs from a different User-Agent string are silently rejected with 401 challenge (chan_sip-faithful AUTH_SECRET_FAILED-equivalent — attacker cannot distinguish UA-mismatch from bad-secret). Hardens against UA-spoofing attacks where an attacker steals credentials but registers from a different SIP client. chan_sip parity sip.h:1268 unsigned short lockuseragent:1 + chan_sip.c:28708-28712 realtime-only parser + chan_sip.c:15839-15843 use-site. chan_sofia surpass: extends parser to config-file too (chan_sip realtime-only is parser-quirk; effect-site fires regardless). chan_sofia surpass: AMI LockUserAgentReject event fires on rejection (Peer + MatchPolicy + LockedUserAgent + Prefixes + AttemptedUserAgent + RemoteAddr) for NMS UA-spoofing-attack visibility (chan_sip silent baseline).
;lockuseragent_prefixes=Yealink SIP-T,Grandstream GRP ; chan_sofia surpass: per-peer comma-separated User-Agent prefix allowlist. Consulted only when lockuseragent=yes. When non-empty, replaces the strict capture-on-first-REGISTER semantic with a vendor-family allowlist: an inbound REGISTER passes when its User-Agent: header starts (case-insensitive) with ANY listed prefix; no match is rejected with the same silent 401 + AMI LockUserAgentReject path (MatchPolicy: prefix-list, Prefixes: <list>). Targets the multi-device-per-peer case (desk phone + softphone on the same credentials) and vendor-family lockdowns (any Yealink T-series, any Grandstream GRP-series). Empty (default) preserves the original strict semantics verbatim. Reload-safe: edit the list in sofia.conf and `module reload chan_sofia.so` — or UPDATE the corresponding realtime column + `sip prune realtime peer <name>` — and the new list is effective on the next REGISTER with no restart.
;accountcode=customer42      ; post-T56 accountcode per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): CDR billing-tag propagated to channel->accountcode for per-customer billing. AST_MAX_ACCOUNT_CODE=20 truncation at CDR-write time (cdr.h:73). chan_sip operator scripts copy verbatim. Per-peer-only — no [general] default_accountcode (chan_sip parity); gabpbx-core ast_default_accountcode at cdr.conf level provides cross-channel default if needed. PRE-EXISTING BUG FIX in this commit: chan_sofia previously passed pvt->username as 5th-arg to ast_channel_alloc (auth identity miscast as accountcode); now passes pvt->accountcode (semantically correct).
;mohinterpret=jazz           ; per-peer MOH class for HOLD-side audio (T26 follow-up); chan_sip parity
;mohsuggest=blues            ; per-peer mohsuggest INBOUND-direction propagation (when this peer holds us, "blues" propagates to bridged channel); OUTBOUND-direction signaling deferred
;language=es                 ; post-T56 language per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): per-peer audio locale propagated to ast_channel.language at sofia_new for prompts/sounds (e.g. en, es, fr, de). Empty (default) inherits [general] language= or gabpbx-core default. chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:28865-28866 verbatim ast_string_field_set + L28447 inheritance. Bounded to channel.h:138 MAX_LANGUAGE=40.
;parkinglot=floor2           ; post-T56 parkinglot per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): per-peer parking-lot routing propagated to ast_channel.parkinglot at sofia_new for Park()/transfer-to-park dialplan operations. Empty inherits [general] parkinglot= ("default" per chan_sip features.h:37 DEFAULT_PARKINGLOT). chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:28890-28891 verbatim ast_string_field_set + L8577 inheritance + L7943-7944 channel propagation.
;defaultip=192.168.1.10      ; post-T56 defaultip per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): fallback IP for host=dynamic peer when not yet registered. Outbound calls before the peer registers route to defaultip; once peer registers src_addr (registration source) takes precedence. Use case: cold-start before registration, or known-fallback for stable upstream gateways. Empty (default) = no fallback (host=dynamic peers fail outbound until registered). chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:28814-28818 verbatim ast_get_ip + L5913-5915 dialog->sa fallback semantic. chan_sofia surpass: resolve-fail logs LOG_WARNING + leaves defaddr empty (chan_sip hard-fails entire build_peer alloc).
;maxcallbitrate=128          ; post-T56 maxcallbitrate per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): per-peer SDP video bandwidth ceiling (kbps) emitted as b=CT:%d media-level attribute. Default 384 per sip.h:218 DEFAULT_MAX_CALL_BITRATE; set 0 to omit b=CT line entirely. Use case: bandwidth-constrained WAN trunks or video peers with QoS limits. Audio calls unaffected (b=CT gated inside if (needvideo) per chan_sip.c:12285). chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:28967-28970 verbatim atoi + bounds-clamp.
;
; post-T56 CID bundle per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in outbound CID override
; for trunk peers): 5 chan_sip-verbatim keys + 1 chan_sofia surpass alias.
; Default empty all 3 fields; channel CID via dialplan CALLERID() takes
; precedence per chan_sip.c:5957 dialog-inheritance Option 6-B semantic
; (peer-CID is base/default — channel CID overrides when set).
;callerid="John Doe" <15554477>  ; combined-form per chan_sip.c:28739-28744 (ast_callerid_split → cid_name + cid_num)
;fullname=John Doe               ; cid_name only per chan_sip.c:28747-28748
;cid_name=John Doe               ; chan_sofia ARCHITECTURAL ADVANTAGE 11th-instance natural-named-field-as-alias for fullname (operator convenience; chan_sip ABSENT)
;cid_number=15554477             ; cid_num only per chan_sip.c:28752-28753
;cid_tag=trunk_eli3              ; per chan_sip.c:28754-28755 — channel-side identifier (Asterisk-internal ast_party_id.tag; NOT SIP From-tag — sofia-sip auto-generates SIP From-tag for dialog uniqueness per RFC 3261 §8.1.1.3)
