;amaflags=billing                ; post-T56 amaflags per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in): per-peer CDR AMA-flags propagated to ast_channel.amaflags at sofia_new for cdr_sqlite3/pgsql/etc. recording. Valid values: "default" / "omit" / "billing" / "documentation" (case-insensitive; see cdr.h ast_cdr_amaflags2int). Empty (default 0) = channel-core default preserved (sofia_new gated on non-zero per chan_sip.c:7947-7948 verbatim). Invalid value → LOG_WARNING + skip-the-bad-key (chan_sip-verbatim semantic). chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:28871-28877 verbatim parser.
;subscribemwi=yes                ; post-T56 subscribemwi per-peer parity (chan_sip drop-in PARSE-COMPAT-ONLY ship; Pattern 12 honest-disclosure 17th-instance NEW sub-pattern chan_sofia-architectural-divergence). chan_sip dual-mode: subscribemwi=no (default) → server pushes UNSOLICITED MWI NOTIFY to peer; subscribemwi=yes → server only NOTIFIES when peer SUBSCRIBEs to message-summary (RFC 6665 + RFC 3842 native subscription model). chan_sofia is SUBSCRIBE-ONLY-BY-DESIGN via T55 sofia_process_mwi_subscribe + transmit_mwi_notify_for_peer architecture; does NOT implement unsolicited MWI NOTIFY. Therefore: (a) subscribemwi=yes operators get drop-in compat zero-rewrite (chan_sofia behavior matches); (b) subscribemwi=no operators get parse-clean migration with LOG_NOTICE at parse-time + KNOWN LIMITATION (chan_sofia behavior remains SUBSCRIBE-only regardless of this setting). Future-fix path: implement peer->mwipvt-equivalent + AST_EVENT_MWI subscription per peer + nua_notify out-of-dialog NOTIFY emission (~100-200 LoC follow-up task if operator demand surfaces). Operator-honest recommendation: migrate UAs to use SUBSCRIBE message-summary mode (modern RFC 6665+RFC 3842 standard). chan_sip parity chan_sip.c:28902-28903 verbatim parser + sip.h:324 SIP_PAGE2_SUBSCRIBEMWIONLY flag bit + 3 use sites L26096+L26978+L29227.
