; ============================================
; Peer configuration options reference
; ============================================
;
; --- Identity ---
; type          - peer, user, or friend (friend = both peer and user)
; secret        - authentication password
; defaultuser   - username for outbound auth (defaults to peer name)
; username      - alias for defaultuser
; user          - alias for defaultuser
; callerid      - caller ID string, e.g. "John Doe" <100>
; regexten      - extension to register
;
; --- Network ---
; host          - hostname, IP, or "dynamic" (default: dynamic)
; port          - remote port (default: 5060)
; transport     - udp, tcp, tls (default: udp). Requires matching listener in [general]
;                 (tlsbindport for tls; ws/wss listeners auto-accept browser UAs).
; nat           - force_rport, comedia, force_rport,comedia (default: none)
;
; --- Dialplan ---
; context       - dialplan context for incoming calls
; fromuser      - user to put in From header
; fromdomain    - domain to put in From header
; insecure      - port, invite, port,invite (or "very")
;                 NOTE (2026-04-27): insecure flag is PARSED but NOT ENFORCED
;                 at runtime — chan_sofia INVITE auth is not implemented today
;                 (REGISTER auth IS implemented; INVITE auth is a separate gap
;                 queued as "post-T56 INVITE digest auth implementation" task).
;                 Use ACL (permit/deny per-peer) + frontend SIP proxy (Kamailio)
;                 + TLS for inbound INVITE protection. See AUDIT.md operational
;                 note + doc/realtime_sippeers.txt Known Limitations.
;
; --- Codecs ---
; disallow      - codecs to disallow (use "all" first, then allow selectively)
; allow         - codecs to allow (see codec list below)
;
; Supported audio codecs: ulaw, alaw, gsm, g722, g729 (annexb=no), g723,
;   opus (/48000/2 channels), speex, speex16, ilbc (mode=20), siren7,
;   siren14, g726, g726aal2, g719, slin, slin16, adpcm, lpc10
; Supported video codecs: h264, h263, h263p, h261, vp8, mp4 (all PT >=96, rate 90000)
;
; Static PTs (RFC 3551): ulaw=0, gsm=3, g723=4, alaw=8, g722=9, g729=18
; Dynamic PTs (96+): assigned by RTP engine — opus, speex, ilbc, h264, vp8, etc.
;
; Example:
; disallow=all
; allow=ulaw
; allow=alaw
; allow=g722
; allow=opus
; allow=h264
;
; --- Media ---
; dtmfmode      - rfc2833, info, inband, auto (default: rfc2833)
; directmedia   - yes/no (allow direct media between endpoints; default: no)
;                 When yes, after the bridge is up chan_sofia issues a re-INVITE
;                 to each leg with the OTHER peer's RTP host:port so RTP flows
;                 directly between the endpoints (PBX out of the media path).
;                 Auto-disabled when nat=force_rport or nat=comedia is set on
;                 either peer (NAT'd peers advertise unreachable private IPs).
;                 488 Not Acceptable from a peer cleanly falls back to relay mode.
;
; --- Registration ---
; expiresecs    - registration expiry in seconds (default: 120)
;               also accepted: defaultexpiry
;
; --- Qualify ---
; qualify       - yes/no or timeout in ms (default: no)
; qualifyfreq   - qualify interval in seconds (default: 60)
; qualifytimeout - qualify timeout in seconds (default: 3)
;
; --- Multi-device ---
; busy_on_active - yes/no: reject new calls with 486 Busy Here when any
;                  device on this account is already in a call (default: no)
; max_contacts   - max simultaneous registered devices per peer;
;                  range [1, 6], default 6, hard ceiling 6
; encryption     - yes/no: SDES-SRTP per RFC 4568 (default: no);
;                  yes requires RTP/SAVP + a=crypto in offer/answer or 488
;
; --- Identity headers (post-T56 identity-headers parity) ---
; callingpres    - default presentation (AST_PRES_*); chan_sip parity values:
;                  allowed_not_screened (default), allowed_passed_screen,
;                  allowed_failed_screen, allowed, prohib_not_screened,
;                  prohib_passed_screen, prohib_failed_screen, prohib, unavailable
; sendrpid       - outbound RPID/PAI emission: no (default), pai (RFC 3325), rpid
; trustrpid      - yes/no: trust inbound PAI/RPID (default: no);
;                  set yes only for trusted upstream proxies / SBCs
;
; --- Call-limit (post-T56 call-limit parity) ---
; callcounter    - yes/no shorthand: yes -> call-limit=INT_MAX (unlimited
;                  tracking, no 480 enforcement); no -> disable (default)
; call-limit     - integer max simultaneous calls per peer; 0 = unlimited
;                  (default). Alias accepted: call_limit (operator-friendly
;                  drop-in form for wiki/forum copy-paste).
; busylevel      - integer soft-cap; outbound returns 486 Busy Here when
;                  inUse >= busy_level (default: 0 = disabled)
;
; ============================================
; T.38 fax UDPTL parity (post-T56 Task #8 SS1-SS7 2026-04-28)
; ============================================
;
; chan_sofia ships full T.38 fax UDPTL parity per RFC 3362 + ITU-T T.38
; mirroring chan_sip behavior verbatim across 11 commits + 8 parallel-audit
; passes (Task #8 SS1+SS1.5+SS2+SS3a+SS3a.1+SS3b+SS4+SS4.1+SS5+SS6+SS7).
;
; Per-peer T.38 keys (mirror chan_sip.c:28038-28063 verbatim):
;
; t38pt_udptl       - T.38 enable + UDPTL EC mode + per-peer MaxDatagram override.
;                     Comma-separated value list:
;                       no                   - T.38 disabled (default)
;                       yes                  - T.38 enabled with EC = FEC (default EC)
;                       fec                  - T.38 enabled with EC = FEC (explicit)
;                       redundancy           - T.38 enabled with EC = Redundancy
;                       none                 - T.38 enabled with EC = None
;                       maxdatagram=N        - per-peer MaxDatagram override (0+)
;                     Examples:
;                       t38pt_udptl = yes,maxdatagram=1400
;                       t38pt_udptl = redundancy
;                       t38pt_udptl = no
;
; t38pt_usertpsource - yes/no: when peer is NAT'd (force_rport or comedia)
;                      AND t38pt_usertpsource=yes, override UDPTL DESTINATION
;                      address with audio's actual seen RTP remote endpoint
;                      (port still taken from m=image). Default: no.
;                      Mirrors chan_sip.c:28061-28063 SIP_PAGE2_UDPTL_DESTINATION
;                      semantic. Required for T.38 fax over NAT'd peers.
;
; faxdetect          - 4-state (no/cng/t38/cng,t38) — see § faxdetect above
;                      for full operator semantics. SS6 (2026-04-28) wired
;                      behaviorally to async-goto fax extension on CNG
;                      detection (audio side) OR peer T.38 reINVITE arrival
;                      (signaling side). Closes 55d4444 KNOWN LIMITATION.
;
; [general] T.38 keys:
;
; t38_maxdatagram      - default T38FaxMaxDatagram override per chan_sip.c:780
; global_t38_maxdatagram - alias for t38_maxdatagram (operator-friendly)
;                        Sentinel `-1` (default) = use built-in 200 bytes.
;                        Positive integer = explicit override.
;                        Per-peer maxdatagram=N sub-option overrides this.
;
; T.38 SIP signaling protection (RFC 3362 §8 + chan_sip.c:24288 verbatim):
;
; chan_sofia arms a 5-second reINVITE-abort timer (sofia_t38_abort callback)
; on T38_PEER_REINVITE entry. If the fax stack does not respond within 5s,
; chan_sofia emits "488 Not Acceptable Here" to the peer + transitions to
; T38_DISABLED. Mirrors chan_sip.c:23396 verbatim semantic. Without this
; timer, peers that fail to ack the 200 OK leave the dialog stuck in
; PEER_REINVITE forever.
;
; chan_sofia surpass dimensions over chan_sip:
;
;   (1) Pattern 16 sofia-sip-native-protocol-mechanics 13th-instance:
;       sdp_media_image + sdp_proto_udptl typed enum dispatch (sofia-sip
;       sdp.h:235 + 249) replaces chan_sip raw sscanf("image %30u udptl t38").
;       Type-safe vs string-parsed; ~5.3x leverage ratio at SS3a inbound parser.
;
;   (2) AMI T38FaxNegotiation event — chan_sofia surpass NEW DIMENSION
;       (helper-arch-advantage 32nd-dim). chan_sip is SILENT on AMI for T.38
;       state transitions (verified 0 hits manager_event.*T38). chan_sofia
;       emits 11-field event at every state transition (DISABLED/LOCAL_REINVITE/
;       PEER_REINVITE/ENABLED) with EVENT_FLAG_SYSTEM:
;         ChannelType: SIP
;         Channel: <chan_name>
;         Uniqueid: <chan_uniqueid>
;         Peer: SIP/<peer_name>
;         State: <Disabled|LocalReinvite|PeerReinvite|Enabled>
;         RequestResponse: <RequestNegotiate|RequestTerminate|Negotiated|
;                           Terminated|Refused|RequestParms>
;         MaxIfp: <unsigned int>
;         MaxDatagram: <unsigned int>
;         Version: <unsigned int>
;         RateManagement: <transferredTCF|localTCF>
;         EC: <FEC|Redundancy|None>
;       AMI consumers should subscribe for fax flow visibility (NMS
;       integration). chan_sip operators currently have NO AMI visibility
;       into T.38 negotiation transitions.
;
;   (3) chan_sofia covers BOTH fd-attach orderings (sofia_new pre-existing
;       udptl + sofia_parse_sdp lazy-create-after-channel-exists) — chan_sip
;       only attaches at sip_new.
;
;   (4) sofia_get_udptl_peer NULL-guard improvement (race-safety post-pvt
;       destruction).
;
; Operational characteristics (audit-disclosed):
;
;   * Reload-mid-fax: existing in-flight T.38 channels NOT affected by
;     reload-time peer->faxdetect_mode change. DSP enable is call-setup-time
;     only (mirrors chan_sip behavior). New calls post-reload pick up new
;     setting.
;
;   * AMI T38FaxNegotiation event spam: fires unconditionally on every state
;     transition. Idempotency early-out at sofia_change_t38_state (chan_sip.c
;     :5772-5773 verbatim) prevents same-state duplicate emits. Under reload-
;     mid-fax or rapid REINVITE/CANCEL races, AMI consumers may see duplicate
;     state transitions — design-preserved-vs-chan_sip.
;
; Test infrastructure for live-fax verification:
;   (a) spandsp soft-fax (sendfax/recvfax CLI from spandsp-utils package)
;   (b) hardware fax + ATA (Cisco SPA112 / Grandstream HT813)
;   (c) Asterisk-with-chan_sip+spandsp peer for fork-test (chan_sofia ↔
;       chan_sip T.38 negotiation interop validation)
;
; Examples:
;
; ; Per-peer T.38 enable with FEC EC + 1400-byte max datagram:
; ;   t38pt_udptl = yes,maxdatagram=1400
; ;   faxdetect = cng,t38
;
; ; Per-peer NAT'd T.38 (peer behind NAT — symmetric-RTP UDPTL destination):
; ;   nat = force_rport
; ;   t38pt_udptl = yes
; ;   t38pt_usertpsource = yes
; ;   faxdetect = t38
;
; ; [general] T.38 default MaxDatagram = 1500 (e.g. matching local MTU):
; ;   t38_maxdatagram = 1500
;
;t38pt_udptl = no                 ; default — T.38 disabled
;t38pt_usertpsource = no          ; default — use SDP c= for UDPTL destination
;t38_maxdatagram = -1             ; default — use built-in 200-byte default
